<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><strong>Last Updated: April 2, 2025</strong></p>
<p>This policy explains how we collect, use, protect, and manage your personal information. eDelphi.org is developed by <strong>Metodix Oy</strong> (data controller) and technically maintained by <strong>Metatavu Oy</strong> (data processor).</p>

<h2>Quick Overview</h2>
<ul>
  <li>We collect limited personal information (name, email address).</li>
  <li>We do NOT sell your data.</li>
  <li>Your Google account data is used solely for authentication and Google Drive integration you explicitly authorize.</li>
  <li>Your data is securely stored and protected within the EU.</li>
  <li>You can always request your data, update it, or ask us to delete it.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<h3>Personal Data You Provide</h3>
<p>When registering with eDelphi.org or logging in via Google, we collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Your first and last name</li>
  <li>Your email address(es)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Google Account Integration</h3>
<p>If you log in using your Google account, we collect:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Google profile information (name, email address)</li>
  <li>Google Drive files explicitly authorized by you (see section Google OAuth Scopes for information)</li>
</ul>
<p>We never collect Google data beyond what you explicitly authorize.</p>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p>We only use your personal and Google user data to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Authenticate and securely identify your account.</li>
  <li>Provide you access to your eDelphi panels.</li>
  <li>Enable import/export of your chosen Google Drive files.</li>
  <li>Provide technical support and improve service functionality.</li>
</ul>

<p>We strictly prohibit and never use your data for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Advertising or marketing.</li>
  <li>Targeting or personalized ads.</li>
  <li>Selling or sharing with data brokers or other unrelated third parties.</li>
  <li>AI model training or similar activities.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
<p>We do not share or transfer, your data to third parties, except:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Secure cloud hosting via Amazon Cloud within the European Union.</li>
  <li>Google Analytics for basic usage tracking (anonymized, aggregated data).</li>
  <li>When legally required or necessary to protect our rights or user safety.</li>
</ul>
<p>All third-party partners must meet strict confidentiality and data security obligations.</p>

<h2>How We Protect Your Data</h2>
<p>Your personal data is securely stored and processed:</p>
<ul>
  <li>On secure, encrypted servers (SSL encryption).</li>
  <li>Within the European Union (Amazon Cloud).</li>
  <li>Accessible only by authorized Metatavu technical personnel.</li>
  <li>Protected by strict access controls, authentication, and monitoring.</li>
</ul>
<p>We regularly review and enhance our security practices to keep your information safe.</p>

<h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
<p>We retain your data:</p>
<ul>
  <li>For the duration of your active use of eDelphi.org.</li>
  <li>Up to 24 months after your last activity, after which inactive user accounts are automatically deleted.</li>
</ul>
<p>You have the right to request immediate data deletion at any time by contacting us directly at <a href="mailto:info@metodix.fi">info@metodix.fi</a>.</p>

<h2>Your Rights</h2>
<p>Under the GDPR and applicable privacy laws, you have the right to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Access your personal data stored by us.</li>
  <li>Correct inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
  <li>Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
  <li>Restrict or object to processing your data.</li>
  <li>Data portability.</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@metodix.fi">info@metodix.fi</a>. We will respond promptly, within the timelines required by law.</p>

<h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
<p>We use cookies solely to enhance your user experience and track basic site usage via Google Analytics. You may disable cookies through your browser settings, but this may impact some features.</p>
<p>We respect your browser's "Do Not Track" settings.</p>

<h2>Compliance</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>GDPR Compliance:</strong> We fully comply with EU Regulation 2016/679.</li>
  <li><strong>COPPA Compliance:</strong> Our services are not intended for users under 16, and we do not knowingly collect data from minors.</li>
  <li><strong>CAN-SPAM Act Compliance:</strong> We use your email solely for transactional purposes (login, support, service updates). You can unsubscribe anytime by contacting us.</li>
  <li><strong>CalOPPA Compliance:</strong> Our policy is always accessible via our website footer.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Google OAuth Scopes</h2>
<p>eDelphi.org uses the following Google OAuth scopes:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>profile</code> scope for identifying users</li>
  <li><code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file</code> scope to allow users to export reports into Google Drive</li>
  <li><code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive</code> scope to allow users to import Google Drive documents into panels they manage. This requires users to share documents with read-only permissions to technical users that act on behalf of the application to allow other users to view imported documents.</li>
</ul>

